4. ğŸ†• Create a Repository on GitHub

Go to GitHub.com â†’ Click the + icon (top right) â†’ New repository.

Name it (e.g., my-docker-project).

âš ï¸ Important: Do not check "Initialize with README" (since you have local code).

5. ğŸš€ Link and Push Follow the commands GitHub shows you under "â€¦or push an existing repository from the command line":

