ğŸ“¦ Part 2: Uploading the Docker Image (GHCR)
If you want to store the actual built image (so people can run docker pull ghcr.io/...), use the GitHub Container Registry.

ğŸ”‘ Prerequisites
You need a Personal Access Token (PAT) from GitHub.

Go to Settings â†’ Developer Settings â†’ Personal access tokens â†’ Tokens (classic).

â˜‘ï¸ Select scopes: write:packages, read:packages, and delete:packages.

ğŸ‘£ Steps
1. ğŸ”“ Login to GitHub Registry via Docker Run this in your terminal (replace USERNAME with your GitHub username):

Bash
export CR_PAT=YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN
echo $CR_PAT | docker login ghcr.io -u USERNAME --password-stdin
2. ğŸ—ï¸ Build your Image with the correct tag You must follow this naming convention: ghcr.io/USERNAME/IMAGE_NAME:TAG

Bash
docker build -t ghcr.io/your-username/my-project:latest .
âš ï¸ Note: Ensure your GitHub username is in lowercase.

3. â˜ï¸ Push the Image Send the built container to the cloud:

Bash
docker push ghcr.io/your-username/my-project:latest
4. âœ… Verify

Go to your GitHub Profile.

Click the Packages tab.

You will see your Docker image listed there! ğŸ‰

